abstracts.cdata!:
The purpose of the Second Technical
            Assistance Project is to help provide financing for
            consulting and engineering services for feasibility,
            pre-investment and other studies and activities, for which
            finance from other sources is not readily available to help
            the Government carry out its program of rehabilitation and
            economic development. The project will thus continue the
            assistance provided by the first Technical Assistance
            Credit. The project includes: (i) detailed engineering of
            Djatiluhur irrigation project; (ii) feasibility study of two
            partially established sugar projects; (iii) seeds industry
            project preparation; (iv) national fertilizer study; and (v)
            groundwater project preparation.
